EmoteActions.Message: I'm Brighteyes. I can't remember my real name. That fool of a Tusker walloped me over the head real good when I arrived here.
I was immediately grabbed after walking through one of those purple swirling portals on Ispar. One of the big walking rugs here grabbed me.
I said, 'Get your hands off me you damn dirty...' then Wunk! A big stone caps me on the head.
They did it to everyone that came here. No people come here anymore though. Stopped about a year ago.
SpokenBrighteyes
I am the leader and only member of the human resistance here in this world gone mad. If you bring me proof that you're fighting against these...these...tuskers. I will reward you.
Give me one of their tusks and I'll be sure to reward you well.
Ooo...ooo...eee...aaa...aaa.
Brighteyes looks around nervously.
I have to keep up appearances that I'm just like the other humans here or else they'll cage and collar me.
What is this? This is the left tusk, it's hollow. I cannot use this. It has no value on this island.
Excellent work. Of course this is one of the lowliest of the tuskers, but you were brave and showed your dedication to my cause.
Take these. If you want I can change your title to be more indicative of your rank within the resistance. All you need do is hand the token back.
The portal gem will get you back here quickly, until you steal the scroll from the clutches of the mighty Bobo.

Now bring me the head of Bobo! Never mind that he calls himself Oolutanga. His minions and Tusker allies can't say that name -- it's too long, has too many vowels. Don't you see? They don't have opposable thumbs! We should be the superior race! We should be ruling them! Don't you get it?
Sorry, I lost it there a little.

So when you bringing me to the mainland?
So when you bringing me to the mainland?
Is it pretty on the mainland? You know calm, no tuskers, people think life is grand?
So you said something about the mainland and me getting to go there someday, right?
Yeah I heard about this place where people get respect even if they are a little off kilter, something about some guy named Martine, you're not from there are you?
So I was thinking maybe you should talk to some friends see if they'll take me in. Or maybe you have a cottage, I can be quiet you know.
Maybe you should to talk to Bobo. Give him a tusker husk for me.
What do you mean, well maybe you should wear a tusker mask...
It's people! Mushed nanners is people!
It gets very lonely out here. I've had a lot of time to myself.
Where did you find this?
You point to the west, towards the place where you found the body.
Along the shore you say? Let me examine this note a little more closely.
Brighteyes studies the scrap of paper given to him.
You are lucky I have learned about their strange methods of communication, otherwise I don't think there'd be an Isparian alive who could translate this.
It seems this particular fellow was taken "below" and given...uh...great power.
And somehow it...ah...opened his mind -- see here, it is indicated with the symbol they use for light.
And here, the symbol for...fighting or war, I think.  It is repeated over and over - I am not sure why.
I'm afraid I can't figure out much else -- however I am quite concerned with this "enlightened" sycophant.  A revolution among the enslaved masses of these islands would be my dream come true!
It would seem as though he was escaping from somewhere "below," on the large island to the west.
Possibly the Tusker Assault lair?  I have heard that subterranean complex is teeming with the beasts and their thralls.
The head of the Painbringer -- I have never heard of such a beast before!
You say you found this vile creature within the Assault lair?
I wonder...is it possible that blasted tusker king has His paw in this new evil?  More powerful minions is not the kind of revolution I had in mind!
Well it isn't much, but...here, take this --
'Tis a bit crude -- but what would you expect?
Brighteyes leans towards you and whispers, "Dammit %s! I'm a tailor, not a weaponsmith!"
This should show everyone who the real champion of Aphus Lassel is!
SpokenBrighteyes

Have you brought me proof that your fighting against the tuskers? If so, hand it over so I can give you your reward. But be discreet, they may not understand Roulean but they know when something is up.
